						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying outside the village.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1759 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record is broken and very much damaged. It seems to have recorded a deed. But with its present condition the exact meaning of it cannot be made out. Gōpāladēva (god), Venkaṇayya, Hālamattarasa-Rāma, Bhairavana-rēkhu (probably a measurement), Sattāgāla, Vīrayya Aya, a son (name lost) of Mudalōja and a son (name lost) of Rukmaya are mentioned.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1681, (Pramathi), Jēshṭha ba. 12. It corresponds to 1759 A.D., June 21, Thursday.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
